1) What kind of Linux machines are you using in your project?

Answer: RHEL (Red Hat Enterprise Linux)

2) How to display Linux version?

cat /etc/os-release or lsb_release -a

3) How to display Kernel version?

uname -r or uname -a

4) How to display all the running processes in Linux OS?

ps -ef

Realtime

top

5) What is a Zombie process in Linux?

A zombie process is a process that has finished execution but still remains in the process table because the parent process has not collected its exit status.

6) How to kill a running process in Linux?

Answer:kill <PID>

Force kill:kill -9 <PID>

By name:pkill process_name

7) How to display the files which are 30 days old in Linux machine?

Answer:find /path -type f -mtime +30

8) How to delete all the files which are 30 days old in Linux machine?

Answer:find /path -type f -mtime +30 -delete

9) What is the difference between find and locate?

Answer:

find searches files in real time and is slower but accurate

locate searches from a database, very fast but may show outdated results


10) How to display all the users who belong to a group?

Answer: getent group groupname
 or
 grep groupname /etc/group


